<Layout title="Grinstead &amp; Snell Ch 8 — Law of Large Numbers" favicon="🎰">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/probability/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to probability</a>

    <h1>Law of Large Numbers</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Grinstead &amp; Snell &middot; GFDL &middot; <a href="https://math.dartmouth.edu/~prob/prob/prob.pdf">PDF</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">The <strong>law of large numbers</strong> says: the sample mean converges to the true mean as the sample grows. Flip a fair coin a million times. The fraction of heads will be close to 0.5. Not because outcomes balance out, but because the noise gets drowned by the signal.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Chebyshev's inequality -->
    <h3>Chebyshev's inequality</h3>
    <p>Before proving the LLN, Grinstead and Snell establish the key tool: <strong>Chebyshev's inequality</strong>. For any random variable X with mean mu and variance sigma^2: P(|X - mu| &ge; k sigma) &le; 1/k^2. The probability of being far from the mean is bounded by the variance. No distributional assumptions needed.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Multiple sample-mean trajectories converging -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 480 240" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Axes -->
        <line x1="50" y1="210" x2="460" y2="210" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <line x1="50" y1="210" x2="50" y2="20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <!-- Y-axis labels -->
        <text x="45" y="120" text-anchor="end" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.5">&#x03BC;</text>
        <text x="45" y="40" text-anchor="end" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.3">1.0</text>
        <text x="45" y="210" text-anchor="end" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.3">0.0</text>
        <!-- X-axis label -->
        <text x="255" y="235" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.5">n (sample size)</text>
